My '62 Morgan 4/4 is basically the same as the original '36 4/4...And the 2003
4/4 is quite the same, again. The sliding pillar front end (original in 1909) 
is
still the same. BTW, '36 was THE big year in Morgan changes...That's the year
Morgan introduced the 4/4 - 4 wheels/4 cylinders - prior to that all Morgans
were "trikes", three wheelers with JAP, Matchless, Blackbourne motorcycle
engines for power...Trikes were in production until '51, the last ones with 
small EnFo (English Ford) engines... :-)
BTW, the grandson of the original founder of the company, now runs it...

